Finally, the names of these two young soldiers will be engraved on headstones as they are laid to rest, alongside thousands of others, with full military honours.

programme.title: World Rally Championship Highlights
programme.desc: Round 13 of the 2025 World Rally Championship is the WRC FORUM8 Rally Japan - the rally first featured in the WRC in 2004 and was held up until 2007 in Hokkaido's Tokachi-Obihiro area before being based in central Hokkaido with Sapporo as the host town in 2008 and 2010. The asphalt event is based in Nagoya on the country's main island of Honshu, and this allows demanding special stages in the mountain regions of Aichi and Gifu that boast a population of approximately nine million people and are about three hours' drive from the capital city of Tokyo. Subaru's Peter Solberg won the inaugural rally in 2004, the winner in 2005 was Peugeot's Marcus Grnholm, and the 2006 winner was Sebastien Loeb with Citroen before Mikko Hirvonen achieved consecutive wins in 2007 and 2008 and Sebastien Ogier won the 2010 edition.
